        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>With the Help of the Almighty God.</p>
            <p><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> Thursday.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Chapter of the week: “You shall command”<lb/> of the year
                    <date>5618</date>.</p>
            <p>Greetings to the highly esteemed father<lb/> the famous scholar Rabbi
                        <sic><addressee>Isaac Lesser</addressee></sic><lb/> in peace &amp; freedom
                will follow surround you till<lb/> the moon will stop to exist
                <sic>exist</sic>.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My dear beloved sir:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Last week I was informed,<lb/> that the directors of the Holy
                Community<lb/> Bnai–Israel intend to elect you, my friend,<lb/> as a judge and
                preside, when the cantor<lb/> will read the <add>[Hebrew]</add> megilah.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>according to the custom of the sons of Israel<lb/> Last Monday was<hi rend="sup"
                    >2</hi> held a meeting<hi rend="sup">1</hi> and the directors<lb/> decided, that
                your Honor shall be one of the judges<lb/> during the time, when the megilah
                    <add>[Hebrew]</add><lb/> will be read on all also to every coming year
                Kal–Midrai <add>[Hebrew]</add><lb/> The directors gave me the <add>Hebrew</add> the
                liberty to send<lb/> you a letter in appreciation and respect due<lb/> to your
                personality and the letter was sent to Mr<lb/> Mr. <persName>S. Blitz</persName>,
                who refused to forward to you, as<lb/> he noticed in the letter many mistakes,
                and<lb/> especially, when the members of the community read<lb/> it when they had
                their meeting on Saturday, and it<lb/> they decided, that such a letter is below the
                dignity<lb/> (or furtige<add>?</add>) of the community, so they applied</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>to me to notify you about and I have my full confidence<lb/> in them and in their
                sayings. I also <sic>inclosed</sic> the<lb/> mentioned above letter in this letter
                and your<lb/> honor shall forgive and return the letter c/o<lb/> the eve. the idea
                is that this incident<lb/> shall remain in strict confidence and shall<lb/> not
                reach any publicity. I hope that you under–<lb/> stand the hint I hope that the hing
                is under–<lb/>stood. And shall your Honor be informed<lb/> that with the coming fast
                of Esther we'll shout<lb/> our <add>Hebrew</add> prayers at 5 p.m.<lb/> and shall
                the lord prolong his your life<lb/> that you'll be able to see all the<lb/> wonders,
                that as God did so our ancestors</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>in the ancient times.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">From me the writer who</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">loves you and remain your</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">obedient servant.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><add>[Hebrew]</add>
                <persName role="author">Simon Picnot</persName>.</p>
        </body>
